Senator Ifeanyi Ubah (Anambra South) has emerged the candidate of the Young Progressives Party (YPP) for the 2023 senatorial poll. Ifeanyi Uba was first elected into the Upper Chamber in 2019. The Senator emerged the flag bearer of the party at a primary held at the Converge Hotel Nnewi on Sunday in Anambra state, according to a statement by Ubah’s media office in Abuja. Ubah, who was returned unopposed, scored 34 votes with one voided vote to emerge the candidate of the party.   What APC should learn from PDP convention     I’m holding collective victory mandate of APC in Ondo South…     Okowa congratulates PDP presidential candidate Atiku   The primary was conducted by the officials from the headquarters of the party led by the National Secretary, Barrister Vidiyeno Baimaiyi and his team. It was witnessed by representatives from the Independent electoral commission (INEC). Ubah pledged to consolidate on his performance so far in the Senate. Hon Peter Uzokwe,who is the former President General of Ozubulu in Ekwusigo Local government area, also emerged candidate of the party for the Nnewi North, Nnewi South and Ekwusigo Federal Constituency.